HEADWORD: Butterbur
<hw>But"ter*bur`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A broad-leaved plant (<spn>Petasites vulgaris</spn>) of the
Composite family, said to have been used in England for wrapping up pats
of butter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

